Our first room, on the top floor was very small (even by European standards) but had a sweet balcony.	The bathroom was in good shape with a full tub and shower, although the tub was quite small compared to North American standards.	The room was miniscule, even by Parisian standards, and very sparsely decorated, although the exposed beams were lovely.	Positives: The staff was incredibly nice and helpful, the room was very clean and a good size for 2 people (by European standards--we stayed in a front side room, which, judging from the reviews, is definitely worth the extra money), beds comfortable, free wifi, AC, and a good sized, delicious breakfast (1 order is more than enough for 2 people).